&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BAND 6 SPECIALIST NURSE, THORACIC SPECIALIST NURSES 32 HOURS PER WEEK &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a dynamic and motivated nurse to join our friendly thoracic specialist nursing team. You will need to be flexible, a team player, and be able demonstrate a commitment to professional development and evidence based practice. As part of the team you will play an integral role in supporting lung cancer patients throughout their cancer journey promoting clinical excellence and the ongoing development of the service. You will be part of the RAPID lung cancer service that supports patients from diagnosis to treatments across sites both at Wythenshawe and Trafford If you feel ready to meet the challenges of this role this could be the opportunity you have been waiting for.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours: 32 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Namekath hewittAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kath Hewitt on 0161 291 4100 or kath.hewitt@mft.nhs.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
